# When the python.exe from a virtual environment is executed, then any _pth file
# located inside the environment's Lib\site-packages folder well ALSO be 'loaded'.
# This can be used to set up the virtual env or to perform checkings.
# But *._pth files does NOT behave like *.py files, we can only put folders paths
# here AND one final 'import' statement.
# So, because we need to run python code, we put here only the import statement
# pointing to the python code we actually want to run, which is 'env_startup.py'

import env_startup    #<--- run 'env_startup.py'
